<subSubSection id="C37B9DF9FFA4FF8C8FC44C7FFCC6A0DC" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA4FF8C8FC44C7FFEF6A71B" blockId="8.[189,310,836,862]" box="[189,310,836,862]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="D096791EFFA4FF8C8FC44C7FFEF6A71B" bold="true" box="[189,310,836,862]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8FC44C7FFEF6A71B" bold="true" box="[189,310,836,862]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA4FF8C8FC44C4EFCC6A0DC" blockId="8.[189,1399,885,1178]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Male abdominal tergites T2 to T4 yellowish with very distinct black stripes or entirely dark brown, T5 with broader stripe or completely black, T6 shiny black (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFA4FF8C8C2C4CA0FC5DA7F3" box="[853,925,923,950]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
); cercal ventral lobe (secondary clasper) fused to cerci with two or three very large curved black medial teeth on the internal margin; surstylus quadrate with a lateral row of strong, short prensisetae on the outer and inner margins (with two medial prensisetae in 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8E1E4B35FDC0A062" authority="Yassin &amp; Suwalski &amp; Raveloson Ravaomanarivo, 2019" authorityName="Yassin &amp; Suwalski &amp; Raveloson Ravaomanarivo" authorityYear="2019" box="[359,512,1037,1063]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chocolata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8E1E4B35FDC0A062" box="[359,512,1037,1063]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. chocolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A226AF1BFFA4FF8C8D704B35FDA8A06D" box="[521,616,1038,1064]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), the innermost one significantly long; hypandrial median process tapering; aedeagus hirsute with fine cuticular scales; posterior parameres as long as aedeagus (slightly shorter in 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8E4F4B61FE0FA036" authority="Yassin &amp; Suwalski &amp; Raveloson Ravaomanarivo, 2019" authorityName="Yassin &amp; Suwalski &amp; Raveloson Ravaomanarivo" authorityYear="2019" box="[310,463,1113,1139]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="chocolata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8E4F4B61FE0FA036" box="[310,463,1113,1139]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. chocolata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A226AF1BFFA4FF8C8EAE4B61FDF5A031" box="[471,565,1114,1140]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
), with finely serrated margins (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFA4FF8C8CDF4B62FBC8A036" box="[934,1032,1113,1139]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1921,1947]" captionTargetBox="[201,1393,1370,1855]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[189,1399,1344,1865]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 3. Photomicrographs of male periphallic organs. A. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). B. D. aff. tsacasi Bock &amp; Wheeler, 1972 (MNHN). C. D. mylenae David &amp; Yassin sp. nov. (MNHN). Scale bars = 0.1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251575/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Figs 3A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFA4FF8C8B6F4B62FBE7A031" box="[1046,1063,1113,1140]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="10.[189,232,1918,1944]" captionTargetBox="[213,1356,343,1838]" captionTargetId="figure@10.[189,1400,300,1865]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="Fig. 5. Male terminalia of the ‘D. seguyi species complex’. A. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). B. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). D–F. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. Scale bars: A–D = 50 µm; E–F = 100 µm.." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251579/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">5</figureCitation>
). Female abdominal tergites lighter than male’s or concolorously dark (
<figureCitation id="135AD2F7FFA4FF8C8DC94B44FD39A0DC" box="[688,761,1151,1177]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="9.[189,232,1889,1915]" captionTargetBox="[253,1334,292,1806]" captionTargetId="figure@9.[228,1359,267,1833]" captionTargetPageId="9" captionText="Fig. 4. Adult habitus. A–B. D. seguyi Smart, 1945 (MNHN). A. ♂. B. ♀. C–D. D. malagassya Tsacas &amp; Rafael, 1982 (MNHN). C. ♂. D. ♀. E–F. D. curta Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas, 1997 (MNHN). E. ♂. F. ♀. G–H. D. chocolata Yassin &amp; David sp. nov. (MNHN). G. ♂. H. ♀. Only dark morphs of females of species with female-limited color dimorphism are shown. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3251577/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C37B9DF9FFA4FF8C8FC44BFFFAF0A27A" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA4FF8C8FC44BFFFEEFA09B" blockId="8.[189,303,1220,1246]" box="[189,303,1220,1246]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
<heading id="D096791EFFA4FF8C8FC44BFFFEEFA09B" bold="true" box="[189,303,1220,1246]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8FC44BFFFEEFA09B" bold="true" box="[189,303,1220,1246]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BDECE72FFA4FF8C8FC44BCEFAF0A27A" blockId="8.[189,1399,1269,1599]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
The original ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8E104BCDFE1DA14A" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[361,477,1270,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8E104BCDFE1DA14A" box="[361,477,1270,1295]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ was renamed ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8C034BCDFC38A14A" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[890,1016,1269,1295]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8C034BCDFC38A14A" box="[890,1016,1269,1295]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ without new definition or justification (
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA4FF8C8E924A20FDBEA170" author="Rafael V." box="[491,638,1307,1333]" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="179 - 189" part="109" refId="ref12862" refString="Rafael V. 1984. Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae). Bulletin de la Societe zoologique de France 109: 179 - 189." title="Relations interspecifiques dans le nouveau complexe africain de Drosophila bakoue du groupe melanogaster, sous-groupe montium (Diptera, Drosophilidae)" type="journal article" year="1984">Rafael 1984</bibRefCitation>
). We consider here the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8CEA4A20FBCBA170" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[915,1035,1307,1333]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8CEA4A20FBCBA170" box="[915,1035,1307,1333]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ to be a junior synonym for the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8EF64A7AFE3EA11F" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[399,510,1345,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8EF64A7AFE3EA11F" box="[399,510,1345,1370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’. 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA4FF8C8DA64A7BFBCEA11E" author="Chassagnard M. - T. &amp; Tsacas L. &amp; Lachaise D." box="[735,1038,1344,1371]" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Natal Museum" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="61 - 131" part="38" refId="ref12068" refString="Chassagnard M. - T., Tsacas L. &amp; Lachaise D. 1997. Drosophilidae (Diptera) of Malawi. Annals of the Natal Museum 38: 61 - 131." title="Drosophilidae (Diptera) of Malawi" type="journal article" year="1997">
Chassagnard 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8C044A7AFC78A11E" box="[893,952,1345,1371]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(1997)
</bibRefCitation>
discussed a ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8BD24A7AFADAA11F" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[1195,1306,1345,1370]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8BD24A7AFADAA11F" box="[1195,1306,1345,1370]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ comprising 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8EB94A5CFDE3A1C5" box="[448,547,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8EB94A5CFDE3A1C5" box="[448,547,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8D4D4A5CFD64A1C5" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[564,676,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8D4D4A5CFD64A1C5" box="[564,676,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8D984A5CFCBDA1C5" authorityName="Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1997" box="[737,893,1383,1408]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyiana">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8D984A5CFCBDA1C5" box="[737,893,1383,1408]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a table legend, but considered all these species members of the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8E9E4AB6FDA2A1E3" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Lachaise" authorityYear="1974" box="[487,610,1420,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bakoue">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8E9E4AB6FDA2A1E3" box="[487,610,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. bakoue</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ in the main text. We restrict here the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8A7F4AB6FAB6A1E3" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[1286,1398,1421,1446]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8A7F4AB6FAB6A1E3" box="[1286,1398,1421,1446]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ to four monophyletic species, while placing 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8CDC4A88FB81A189" authorityName="Chassagnard &amp; Tsacas" authorityYear="1997" box="[933,1089,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyiana">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8CDC4A88FB81A189" box="[933,1089,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the ‘ 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8BD84A88FAD8A189" authorityName="Bock &amp; Wheeler" authorityYear="1972" box="[1185,1304,1459,1484]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tsacasi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8BD84A88FAD8A189" box="[1185,1304,1459,1484]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. tsacasi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species complex’ (see below). 
<bibRefCitation id="EFF0B383FFA4FF8C8EAA4AE3FD7EA1B6" author="David J. R. &amp; Yassin A. &amp; Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V." box="[467,702,1496,1523]" journalOrPublisher="Annales de la Societe entomologique de France" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" pagination="336 - 342" part="50" refId="ref12333" refString="David J. R., Yassin A., Gidaszewski N. &amp; Debat V. 2014. Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands. Annales de la Societe entomologique de France 50: 336 - 342. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00379271.2014.938548" title="Drosophilids (Diptera) from Mayotte island: an annotated list of species collected in 2013 and comments on the colonisation of Indian Ocean Islands" type="journal article" year="2014">
David 
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8D5F4AE2FDA5A1B7" box="[550,613,1496,1522]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">et al.</emphasis>
(2014)
</bibRefCitation>
referred to three of these species as geographical strains of 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8F994AC4FE53A25D" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[224,403,1534,1560]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8F994AC4FE53A25D" box="[224,403,1534,1560]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with partial reproductive isolation. Closer examination of their material revealed, however, that each strain was a distinct species (namely, 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8C21491EFC07A27B" authorityName="Smart" authorityYear="1945" box="[856,967,1573,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="seguyi">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8C21491EFC07A27B" box="[856,967,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. seguyi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8CAF491EFB45A27B" authorityName="Tsacas &amp; Rafael" authorityYear="1982" box="[982,1157,1572,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="malagassya">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8CAF491EFB45A27B" box="[982,1157,1572,1598]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. malagassya</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C61B5F1FFA4FF8C8BC4491EFADFA27B" box="[1213,1311,1573,1598]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Drosophila" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="curta">
<emphasis id="B9151260FFA4FF8C8BC4491EFADFA27B" box="[1213,1311,1573,1598]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">D. curta</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
